"title": "5741: vows",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5741: vows",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Promises made to God, usually in the context of worship or religious practice. There was no requirement on any Israelite to make vows, but once made, they were binding and had to be kept.</p>\n<h2>Vows were binding</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:21-Deut23:23\">DEU 23:21–23:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num30:2\">NUM 30:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num30:9\">NUM 30:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:25\">PRO 20:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:4-Eccl5:6\">ECC 5:4–5:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal1:14\">MAL 1:14</a></p>\n<h3>Exceptions to keeping vows</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num30:3-Num30:8\">NUM 30:3–30:8</a></strong> <em>In certain cases vows made by daughters or wives could be nullified by fathers or husbands respectively.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num30:10-Num30:15\">NUM 30:10–30:15</a></p>\n<h2>Vows made to God in the context of worship</h2>\n<h3>To offer sacrifices</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:17-Lev22:19\">LEV 22:17–22:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:16\">LEV 7:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:21\">LEV 22:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:9\">LEV 27:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:2-Num15:4\">NUM 15:2–15:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:8-Num15:10\">NUM 15:8–15:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:6\">DEU 12:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:11\">DEU 12:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps50:14\">PSA 50:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps66:13\">PSA 66:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:14\">PRO 7:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah2:9\">JON 2:9</a></p>\n<h3>To dedicate people, animals or property to God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:1-Lev27:25\">LEV 27:1–27:25</a></strong></p>\n<h3>To give money</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs12:4-2Kgs12:5\">2KI 12:4–12:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:18\">DEU 23:18</a></p>\n<h2>Motives for making vows</h2>\n<h3>To elicit God's help</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:11\">1SA 1:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:20-Gen28:22\">GEN 28:20–28:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num21:2\">NUM 21:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg11:30-Judg11:40\">JDG 11:30–11:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam15:7-2Sam15:8\">2SA 15:7–15:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps66:13-Ps66:14\">PSA 66:13–66:14</a></p>\n<h3>To express thanksgiving</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps116:12-Ps116:14\">PSA 116:12–116:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps50:14\">PSA 50:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps56:12\">PSA 56:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps116:17-Ps116:18\">PSA 116:17–116:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah1:16\">JON 1:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah2:9\">JON 2:9</a></p>\n<h3>To praise God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:25\">PSA 22:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps61:8\">PSA 61:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps65:1\">PSA 65:1</a></p>\n<h2>Vows of Nazirites</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:1-Num6:21\">NUM 6:1–6:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg13:2-Judg13:5\">JDG 13:2–13:5</a> <em>Samson was set apart as a Nazirite from birth</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:11\">1SA 1:11</a> <em>Samuel may have been a Nazirite.</em></p>\n<h2>Examples of vows made to God</h2>\n<h3>By David</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps132:2-Ps132:5\">PSA 132:2–132:5</a></strong></p>\n<h3>By Paul</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:18\">ACT 18:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:24-Acts21:26\">ACT 21:24–21:26</a></p>\n<h2>Abuse of vows</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:5-Matt15:6\">MAT 15:5–15:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:11-Mark7:13\">MRK 7:11–7:13</a></p>\n<h2>Vows made to idols</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer44:25-Jer44:28\">JER 44:25–44:28</a></strong></p>",
